header.gameNote: 2009 HISPANIC COLLEGE FUND CLASSIC AT KENT OH

article.headline: UAB 68, Green Bay 56
article.story: KENT, Ohio -- Elijah Millsap scored 22 points and grabbed 11 rebounds to lead Alabama-Birmingham to a 68-56 win over Wisconsin-Green Bay in the season opener for both teams on Friday. Howard Crawford added 15 points for the Blazers, who went on a 14-2 run to claim a 55-43 lead with 4:50 left the second half against the Phoenix in the Hispanic College Fund Classic. Crawford, who shot 7-for-11 from the field, led the spurt with six points and Kenneth Cooper added four points. UAB pushed its margin to 15 points -- its largest of the game -- on Cameron Moore's layup with 1:42 left to play. Cooper also had seven points and 11 rebounds, and Millsap shot 5 of 6 from beyond the arc. Rahmon Fletcher led Wisconsin-Green Bay with 14 points, while Bryquis Perine had 13. The Blazers outrebounded the Phoenix 40-29.
